  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Bowel cleansing</measure>
    <time_frame>1 year</time_frame>
    <description>Boston Bowel Preparation Score (BBPS), a 10-point scale assessing bowel preparation after all cleansing maneuvers are completed by the endoscopist. Each region of the colon receives a &quot;segment score&quot; from 0 to 3 and these segment scores are summed for a total BBPS score ranging from 0 to 9. Therefore, the maximum BBPS score for a perfectly clean colon without any residual liquid is 9 and the minimum BBPS score for an unprepared colon is 0.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
